MYNDERSE STUDENTS PARTICIPATE IN CENTENNIAL FOUNTAIN DEDICATION

As the new Centennial Fountain was dedicated today by NYS Lieutenant Governor Kathy Hochul, Mynderse Academy students kayaked in the Cayuga-Seneca canal to help celebrate the event. SFCSD Board member, Joell Murney-Karsten, who also serves as the Chair for the Seneca Falls Development Corporation, also spoke at today's dedication. Superintendent Jeramy Clingerman was also at the event.

Mynderse Academy students who participated in the ceremony today were: Alyssa Marley, Mya Soto, Alyssa Karsten, LaToya Soura, Isabel Wager, Mansi Trivedi, Rya Swenson, Tristan Shell, Macy Benz, and Emily Cook.

The Centennial Fountain features a pump that was provided by Seneca Falls company, ITT Goulds Pumps. The fountain will be on display in the canal until September 8th, and will light up each night with purple, gold and white lights - the colors of the American suffrage movement.

What a great way to celebrate our community and the powerful movement that changed lives forever. #SFCSDPROUD #19thAmendment #WomensVote100 #SenecaFalls

post_text:
LANDO VISITS THE WHITE HOUSE

On Monday, Mynderse Academy rising sophomore Grace Lando visited the White House for a ceremony that unveiled the Building the Movement Exhibit, which features one original piece from each state that celebrates 100 years of women's suffrage. Grace's artwork was chosen to represent New York State and featured suffragettes Ida B. Wells and Alice Paul. Grace also had a tour of the White House and met the First Lady.

Below is a link to a short video with highlights of the ceremony. Soon, the White House will display the exhibit virtually - and we will pass along the link when we have it. So proud of you Grace! #SFCSDPROUD #MynderseArt

First Lady Melania Trump FingerLakes1.com Finger Lakes Times Pam Helming Democrat and Chronicle

https://www.instagram.com/tv/CEU_YAOghc0/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link

SENIOR SWEETS AND TREATS

On Monday, June 22 - to kick off graduation week, our Mynderse Academy Seniors got a special treat in the bus loop of the Academy. Seniors were able to choose an ice cream treat from the Sprinkle Starship - an ice cream truck owned by Mynderse Academy alumni Paige Montgomery ('18), and receive cookies made by alumni and Mynderse Academy Special Education teacher Bethany Boyes ('01). Seniors then were asked to sign a large Block M to commemorate their time at Mynderse Academy and it will hang in the school in their honor. #MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD #Classof2020 #sweetsandtreats

Seneca Falls Central School District added 126 new photos.
June 29 at 3:20 PM ·

In an unusual year, the Seneca Falls Middle School found a way to celebrate the 8th Graders who will be heading down the hall to attend Mynderse Academy as freshmen in the fall.

On Wednesday, June 24, 2020, families gathered in their vehicle to drive through the bus loop at the Middle School/High School complex and stop at stations to receive their certificates, awards, t-shirts, cookies and a whole lot of love from their teachers and administrators!

Congratulations to the new rising freshmen at Mynderse Academy and welcome to the Class of 2024! #MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD #BLUEDEVILNATION

post_text:
Mynderse Academy Commencement

The 146th Mynderse Academy Commencement will be held tomorrow, Friday, June 26, 2020 on Bracht Field, with ceremonies at 6:00 PM and 7:15PM.The rain date will be Sunday, June 28th at 11:00 AM and 12:15 PM. Due to COVID-19 and the restrictions in place by Governor Cuomo's Executive Order, there will be two ceremonies this year. Admission for the ceremonies will be by ticket only as there is a maximum capacity of 150, including graduates. There will be physically distant assigned seating, and all attendees must wear a face covering. More details can be found on the front page of our website.

For all other friends and family of Mynderse Academy and the Class of 2020, both ceremonies will be live-streamed by our friends at Fingerlakes1. Please use the link below to see the ceremonies.

Please join us online to wish the Class of 2020 the best.

Together.
We are family.
We are Mynderse.
#MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD
#onceabluedevilalwaysabluedevil

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=drjJgY1FN_g

post_text:
8TH GRADE PROMOTION TONIGHT

8th Grade Promotion will be held this evening from 6:00 - 8:00 PM in the bus loop at the Mynderse Academy. Due to COVID-19, there will be a celebratory drive-by where students will receive their promotion certificates and awards form their 8th grade teachers. Students are invited to come anytime between 6:00 - 8:00 PM and please only bring one car per family. Please pull into the student parking lot across from Bracht Field where you see balloons and Enter/Exit signs and wait for instructions. You will then be directed into the bus loop and slowly proceed and stop at all tents. Please remain in your vehicle at all times.

If you are unable to attend, or the weather doesn't allow the promotion to occur, 8th grade teachers will be hand delivering certificates to your house on June 25 from 2:00 - 4:00 PM.

Congratulations to our 8th Graders - the new Mynderse Academy Class of 2024! #SFCSDPROUD

Students are invited to come anytime between 6:00 - 8:00 PM and please only bring one car per family. Please pull into the student parking lot across from Bracht Field where you see balloons and Enter/Exit signs and wait for instructions. You will then be directed into the bus loop and slowly proceed and stop at all tents. Please remain in your vehicle at all times.

If you are unable to attend, or the weather doesn't allow the promotion to occur, 8th grade teachers will be hand delivering certificates to your house on June 25 from 2:00 - 4:00 PM.

Congratulations to our 8th Graders - the new Mynderse Academy Class of 2024! #SFCSDPROUD

SUMMER MEAL PLANNING

The Seneca Falls Central School District is working on a plan to make sure our students have access to meals throughout the summer break. We are requesting feedback below to help us in our planning for this.

The Summer Meal Program will be provided through pick up only at four locations, two days a week (Tuesday and Thursday).

Even if your child does not currently receive free or reduced lunch, they are eligible for summer meals at no cost.

Please complete the following survey by June 18.

School Budget Vote

As per the State of New York Executive Order No. 202.26, the annual vote and election has been rescheduled to Tuesday, June 9, 2020 and will be held by Absentee Ballot. Ballots are currently being printed and residents should receive them by June 1st. If you have not received your Absentee Ballot by June 2, 2020, please contact the District at (315) 568-5818. Follow the instructions in the ballot and mail the ballot back or deliver it to the District Office (98 Clinton Street) drop box by 5:00 PM on June 9, 2020.

A Virtual Budget Hearing will be held via Zoom at 6:00 PM on Monday, June 1, 2020 (https://senecafallscsd.zoom.us/j/83844542485?pwd=LzBYbGc4YjgwNGR2d2xwSEtpZytiUT09).

Please visit the district's budget webpage for all budget information (including a voiceover budget presentation video): https://www.senecafallscsd.org/Page/119

QUICK REMINDER FOR PARENTS AND STUDENTS

Packet pick-up and drop-off is TODAY from 3-6PM!

We are requesting that parents pick up the new lessons/materials at the main entrance of the building your child(ren) attend. There will be administrators, faculty and staff at the main entrance of each building to provide you with your child(ren)’s lessons/materials. Also at this time, you will be dropping off all completed work. Please make sure the student’s name and teacher’s name is on each paper or at least the front page if they are stapled together.

Please do not exit your vehicle when picking up lessons/materials. We will ask for your child(ren)’s name and bring their lessons/materials to the vehicle. We need to continue adhering to the physical distancing procedures to protect ourselves.

Looking forward to seeing you all later today!
#SFCSDPROUD

post_text:
SENECA FALLS HONORS CLASS OF 2020

Drive down Fall Street in Seneca Falls today and things may look a little different!

The Seneca Falls community found a way to highlight this special Senior Class of 2020 by coming together and organizing a special tribute.

Two community members, Angela Anderson and Autumn DeVries organized an online fundraiser which raised over $4500 to honor the seniors with posters downtown! They coordinated with the school district and Brad VanDusen to make posters of each senior to hang downtown from the light posts. Ferrara Lumber donated the zip ties that were used to hang the posters and the Seneca Falls Fire Department also volunteered their time to help hang them up. Once the project was finished and paid for, Anderson and DeVries donated the extra funds - $2400 back to Project Graduation for the Class of 2020.

Many thanks to all who contributed in some way to this special honor for our seniors. We continue to be so proud of our community partnerships!
#MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD
Brad VanDusen Photography FingerLakes1.com
Finger Lakes Times

post_text:
The Seneca County Community Counseling Center Prevention Team is offering both Individual and group support for students and parents via Zoom meetings. The group forum for parents will offer the opportunity to exchange information, find emotional support and offer guidance on resources.

Individual services will include opportunities for emotional support and skills building (i.e. coping skills, motivating students to learn remotely, stress reduction, mindfulness or a referral to outside resources for additional support.)

Please reach out to one of the following Prevention Counselors to sign up for either individual or group support.

Seneca Falls School District: Michelle Joseph - mjoseph@senecafallscsd.org or Darlene Bennett - dbennett@senecafallscsd.org.

#SFCSDPROUD

post_text:
SEUSSICAL

What an incredible show! You still have three more opportunities to see it - today at 2:00 and 7:30 PM and tomorrow at 2:00.

However, due to Governor Cuomo's recent restrictions on the number of people who can attend a social event due to COVID-19, we can only allow 190 people to attend each performance.

The good news is that the show can still be performed, but unfortunately, we will have to turn people away once we reach 190. We are sorry about the limitations this puts on the number of people who can attend each show, but we hope over the course of the three shows that are left, everyone who wants to attend will be able to. All tickets will be sold at the door.

#SFCSDPROUD #Seussical

post_text:
LAPRADE AND PHOTHIRATH CHOSEN FOR NYSBDA FESTIVAL

Congratulations to Mynderse Academy senior Kobe LaPrade and Seneca Falls Middle School 8th Grader Katherine Phothirath for their participation in the #NYSBDA2020 Honor Jazz Ensemble and Honor Concert Band! Both students were able to travel to Syracuse with Band Director Laura FitzGerald this past weekend to participate in the #NYSBDA2020 Festival.

Katherine was selected for the Middle School Honor Band, which included over one hundred 7th and 8th grade students from around the state. Kobe was selected for the second year in a row to participate in the High School Honor Jazz Ensemble. Only 18 students from across the state were selected for this group! Both students had an incredible experience and the concerts were outstanding! We are so proud of you both! #SFCSDPROUD #MynderseMusic #NYSBDA2020 #MusicInOurSchoolsMonth

IT'S CAKE WEEK AT MYNDERSE!

Mynderse Academy Food Prep classes spent this week learning how to make, bake, decorate and serve a cake. Mrs. Willson's lessons are always incredibly fun, hands on and she even brought in Art teacher Mrs. Korba to help with decorating. Once their creation was complete, students learned how to slice and serve the cake, and pieces were delivered to teachers who judged and graded their work. The whole week was fun for everyone! CAKE WEEK ROCKS!

Next up for Food & Culture classes? Regional foods. Jambalaya anyone? #MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD #cakeweek #delicious #teachskillsforlife

At Mynderse Academy, Ceramics Class has students working hard on the wheel learning how to create pots and bowls, while other students are learning how to use coils to make different pieces. In Advanced Art, their latest project was to create a ceramic piece and then create a painting on its surface using underglaze. Teacher Mrs. Korba just got the last of them out of the kiln today. Fantastic work!

Mynderse Academy will be hosting a blood drive this Friday, March 6th in the Gym from 8:00 AM - 2:00 PM. This drive will be open to students and the public.

You must be 17 or older, or 16 with parent consent, and at least 110 pounds.

On Friday, community members will come in through front door and sign in with the Main Office (you will need a valid NYS ID) before going to Gym.

If you are interested in participating, please email Emily James ejames@senecafallscsd.org for more information and to sign up.

All who come to donate will receive a free Red Cross Water Bottle!

post_text:
RECORD-SETTING INDOOR TRACK SEASON ENDS

Last Saturday, seven Mynderse athletes competed in Section Five’s qualifying meet for the New York State Indoor Track Championship to be held in Staten Island this weekend. The seven athletes were Rachel Mahoney and Carter Puylara in the sprint hurdles, Margaux Eller in the 1500 meter run, Karrina McKoy in the shot put and Margaux, Hannah Weston, Alliyah Adams and Kaitlyn Hilkert in the 4 x 800 relay. No one advanced to States, but Margaux did set a school record in the 1500 meters!

Thanks to all of our athletes for a tremendous season - and especially to our 14 seniors for their hard work and dedication to our team! You will all be missed!

#SFCSDPROUD #BLUEDEVILNATION #onceabluedevilalwaysabluedevil #Classof2020

post_text:
Capital Project Vote 2020

The Facilities Committee and Seneca Falls Board of Education are happy to report that the Capital Project Vote passed 206 (yes) to 52 (no). We want to thank each community member who was able to cast a vote. We also want to thank the community for their continued support of the District and allowing us the opportunity to continue to invest in our facilities and programs.

We will continue to provide updates on the project through the District’s website once the work begins. We will know more in the coming weeks regarding the timeline for construction.

Sincerely,
Jeramy Clingerman
Superintendent of Schools
Seneca Falls CSD

Congratulations to the Mynderse Academy Girls Indoor Track program as they won their first individual Sectional title in program history! The 4 x 800 Relay Team of Hannah Weston, Aaliyah Adams, Margaux Eller and Kaitlyn Hilkert took home the prize by finishing three seconds before second-place LeRoy. We are so proud of you! Congratulations to our champions - and good luck at State Qualifiers this weekend! GO MA!!! #MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD #CHAMPIONS #bringithome

Pictured from left - Margaux Eller, Kaitlyn Hilkert, Coach Porter, Aaliyah Adams and Hannah Weston.

BASKETBALL SECTIONALS BEGIN THIS WEEK

The regular season for our basketball teams has wrapped up and both the Boys and Girls teams are headed into the play-offs this week with two home games.

Mynderse Boys Basketball will take on Early College on Wednesday, Febraury 26th here at home at 7:00 PM. The game will be held in the Middle School Gym (200 Mynderse St, Seneca Falls) and admission will be $5 per person. Concession stand will be open.

The Mynderse Girls Basketball team plays the Haverling Lady Rams on Friday, February 28th here in the Middle School Gym with tip-off at 7:00 PM. Admission is $5 per person and there will be a concession stand available.

Come out and cheer for our Blue Devils as they start their battle for a championship! GO MA!!! #MAPROUD #SFCSDPROUD #BLUEDEVILNATION #bringhometheblock

***Please note that all sectional games have a $5 per person admission fee. This is set by Section V and not our local school.***
